1800 degrees Fahrenheit.

00:10:58.460 --> 00:11:00.330
That's really hot you
don't want to live there.

00:11:00.330 --> 00:11:01.800
We don't think it's
a habitable planet.

00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:05.320
And then as we start
thinking about what that means

00:11:05.320 --> 00:11:10.440
to be habitable we start to get
a sense that planets like earth,

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:12.660
maybe Venus, maybe Mars, are

00:11:12.660 --> 00:11:16.090
in a region near our star
called the Goldilocks zone,

00:11:16.090 --> 00:11:20.140
where they're not too hot for
water to exist on the surface

00:11:20.140 --> 00:11:23.320
and they're not too cold for
