00:11:27.930 --> 00:11:30.440
And exoplanet discovery
started to take off.

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:34.450
There are several different methods
you can use to discover exoplanets.

00:11:34.450 --> 00:11:39.530
And so in 2009 NASA finally
completed a mission called Kepler.

00:11:39.530 --> 00:11:43.480
Kepler was actually dreamed
of decades before it was built

00:11:43.480 --> 00:11:47.000
and launched by principal
investigator Bill Borucki.

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:49.290
He knew theoretically,
he wrote a paper,

00:11:49.290 --> 00:11:52.430
that said if you were very
careful with your photometry,

00:11:52.430 --> 00:11:56.720 position:56%
