year, once every 365 days.

00:14:57.940 --> 00:15:01.560
We have to be perfectly aligned
in order that that planet passes

00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:03.710
in front of the star
as we're viewing it

00:15:03.710 --> 00:15:05.920
from our vantage point
in the Milky Way.

00:15:05.920 --> 00:15:07.900
It turns out that we
expect only about one

00:15:07.900 --> 00:15:11.310
in a hundred stars are
going to be aligned with us

00:15:11.310 --> 00:15:13.070
so that we would see transits.

00:15:13.070 --> 00:15:14.880
So you have to look
at a lot of them.

00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:18.330
