00:43:06.480 --> 00:43:09.460
&gt;&gt; A distant star is
orbited by two planets.

00:43:09.460 --> 00:43:13.520
One looks similar to the earth,
the other is a gas giant.

00:43:13.520 --> 00:43:16.500
When viewed from a distance
the two planets disappear

00:43:16.500 --> 00:43:18.700
into the glare of their sun.

00:43:18.700 --> 00:43:22.520
How could we ever find these
planets all the way from the earth?

00:43:22.520 --> 00:43:25.330
By using a space telescope
with the coronagraph

00:43:25.330 --> 00:43:28.590
to separate star light
from planet light.

00:43:28.590 --> 00:43:32.590
As the stars light passes through
the telescopes large mirrors,

00:43:32.590 --> 00:43:35.060
it picks up small distortions.

00:43:35.060 --> 00:43:39.130
Diffraction adds concentric
rings to the image we see.

00:43:39.130 --> 00:43:42.670
To reveal the planets, first
a coronagraph uses a mask

00:43:42.670 --> 00:43:44.650
to block much of the stars light

00:43:44.650 --> 00:43:48.390
and redirect the remaining
light to the outer edges.

00:43:48.390 --> 00:43:53.700 position:56%
A washer shaped device can now block
most of the rest of the stars light.

00:43:53.700 --> 00:43:58.000
Because the planets light comes
in at an angle, it misses the mask

00:43:58.000 --> 00:44:00.440
and passes through the
center of the washer.

00:44:00.440 --> 00:44:04.160
But when we turn up the image
signal by collecting more light,

00:44:04.160 --> 00:44:06.880
we can see that the
planets are still hidden

00:44:06.880 --> 00:44:09.980
under blobs of leftover star light.

00:44:09.980 --> 00:44:13.680 position:56%
To remove these blobs the
coronagraph has a special deformable

00:44:13.680 --> 00:44:17.590
mirror that can change shape by
using hundreds of tiny pistons.

00:44:17.590 --> 00:44:21.510
This can correct distortions
in the light beam.

00:44:21.510 --> 00:44:24.640
As the mirror deforms,
the blobs of light as seen

00:44:24.640 --> 00:44:27.230
in the monitor slowly
begin disappearing,

00:44:27.230 --> 00:44:31.250
finally revealing the
brighter of the two planets.

00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:35.860
Afterwards, the fainter
planet also comes into view.

00:44:35.860 --> 00:44:41.320 position:56%
We can now see objects more than a
billion times fainter than the star.

00:44:41.320 --> 00:44:43.480
And if the light from
